<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36209e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36209e">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36209e"> 209(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Daniel VIII 13-14 <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n36209e"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[A brief history of Sects.]</font> <font color="green">[The church of the Seventh Day Adventists]</font> originated in 1845-1846 upon the interpretation of <mark>Daniel VIII,13-14</mark>: &ldquo;Then shall the sanctuary be cleansed&rdquo;&mdash;as meaning that heaven was here, since the date of 1844, set as the coming of the Kingdom, was correct. <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 449</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
